snippet: Senator John D. Rockefeller IV of West Virginia announced that he would not seek a sixth term in 2014, providing an opening for Republicans to cut into the Democratic Senate majority.
abstract: West Virginia Sen John D Rockefeller IV, longtime liberal voice in Congress, says he will not seek a sixth term in 2014, providing opening for Republicans to cut into Democratic Senate majority in upcoming election.
lead_paragraph: Senator John D. Rockefeller IV of West Virginia announced that he would not seek a sixth term in 2014, providing an opening for Republicans to cut into the Democratic Senate majority.

headline.main: Rockefeller Will Leave Senate After Five Terms
headline.print_headline: Rockefeller Will Leave Senate After Five Terms
